Configuring the command prompt to show the branch:

__git_ps1

How to configure prompt in Unix:
echo $PS1
export PS1='----->'

export PS1='\W$(__git_ps1 "(%s)") > '

cd ~

nano .bash_profile

export PS1='\W$(__git_ps1 "(%s)") > '

In widnows Do the same thing by creating a .bash_profile file inside the "User directory":

source ~/.bash_profile
